		<div id="comment_body_69170"><p>It might please you to learn that Web.pm aims to have a full port of Rack at its core. The idea is that people should be able to choose the level of abstraction they want to build their web app on. The levels are something along the lines of:</p><ul>
  <li>A minimal setup. (Rack.)</li><li>Templating.</li><li>MVC.</li></ul><p>That last level is the reason I'm investigating MVC frameworks at present.</p></div>
		
	
	</div>
